decision_conditions:
&lt;p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:pre-wrap&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:0cm;
text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:10.5pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;color:black&quot;&gt;Part of the ground floor of the
site known as 103 Morning Lane is already shown to be in use for residential
purposes. The proposal therefore fails to comply with Class MA.1.(1) (b) of
Schedule 2, Part 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted
Development) (England) (Order) 2025 (as amended).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:pre-wrap&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:0cm;
text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:10.5pt;
font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;color:black&quot;&gt;Two Article 4 Directions made by
Hackney Borough Council are presently in force for this site which have removed
permitted development rights for change of use from Class E (Commercial,
Business and Service) to Class C3 (Dwellinghouses) comprised within Class MA of
Schedule 2, Part 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted
Development) (England) (Order) 2025 (as amended).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:0cm;margin-left:0cm;
text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The applicant has failed to make a
S106 agreement commitment to car-free development for this proposal.&amp;nbsp; The proposal is
therefore contrary to Policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of the
Hackney Local Plan 2033 (LP33) (Adopted July 2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
